OL,3,CDefiant Starmer set for key meeting
OL,4,Cwith Streeting ahead of King's Speech
OL,6,FStreeting was seen as the biggest
OL,7,Fthreat to Starmer's immediate
OL,8,Fleadership, with his other rivals,
OL,9,FGreater Manchester mayor Andy Burnham,
OL,10,Fnot an MP, and former Deputy Prime
OL,11,FMinister Angela Rayner appearing
OL,12,Freluctant to throw her hat in the ring.
OL,14,FBurnham needs an MP willing to stand
OL,15,Faside so he can fight a by-election.
OL,17,FSources close to Energy Secretary Ed
OL,18,FMiliband, another potential soft-left
OL,19,Fchallenger, have denied reports that
OL,20,Fhe is preparing to run if Streeting
OL,21,Ftriggers a contest.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1778746039
OL,3,CDefiant Starmer set for key meeting
OL,4,Cwith Streeting ahead of King's Speech
OL,6,FThe prime minister has sought to push
OL,7,Fon, already having replaced four
OL,8,Fministers ` including prominent MP
OL,9,FJess Phillips and health minister
OL,10,FZubir Ahmed, an ally of Streeting `
OL,11,Fwho quit the Government and called for
OL,12,FStarmer to stand down.
OL,14,FIn Tuesday's Cabinet meeting, Starmer
OL,15,Fvowed to fight on, and was publicly
OL,16,Fbacked by several ministers at the top
OL,17,Fof government, including his deputy
OL,18,FDavid Lammy, who urged colleagues to
OL,19,F"step back and take a breath".
OL,26,@{D@AOU{D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
